37    /**
38    * Abstract implementation for calendar systems that use a typical
39    * day/month/year/leapYear model.
40    * Most of the utility methods required by subclasses are package-private,
41    * reflecting the intention that they be defined in the same package.
42    * <p>
43    * BasicChronology is thread-safe and immutable, and all subclasses must
44    * be as well.
45    *
46    * @author Stephen Colebourne
47    * @author Brian S O'Neill
48    * @author Guy Allard
49    * @since 1.2, renamed from BaseGJChronology
50    */
